An Act
ENROLLED SENATE
BILL NO. 1437 By: Pugh and Hamilton of the
Senate
and
Sterling and Stinson of the
House
An Act relating to schools; creating the President
Donald J. Trump Physical Fitness Act; providing short
title; directing the State Department of Education to
establish certain guidelines to administer certain
physical fitness test; directing guidelines to be
based on certain recommendations; providing for
contents of guidelines; requiring school districts to
administer certain test after certain guidelines have
been established; directing school districts to use
student performance results in certain manner;
providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
noncodification; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
SUBJECT: Physical fitness test
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
This act shall be known and may be cited as the “President
Donald J. Trump Physical Fitness Act”.
SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-103.9c of Title 70, unless
there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:

A. The State Department of Education shall establish guidelines
for school districts in this state to assess the overall fitness of
students and encourage physical activity and healthy habits by
administering the Presidential Fitness Test. The physical fitness
test guidelines shall be based on the recommendations of the
President’s Council on Sports, Fitness, and Nutrition, which was
reconstituted by Executive Order 14327. The guidelines shall
include:
1. Training for personnel to administer the test;
2. Exemption guidelines for students with disabilities, medical
conditions, or other factors that would impact their ability to
complete the test; and
3. An option for a parent or legal guardian of a student to opt
the student out of the test.
B. Upon development of the physical fitness test
recommendations by the President’s Council on Sports, Fitness, and
Nutrition and the subsequent establishment of guidelines by the
State Department of Education, school districts in this state shall
administer the Presidential Fitness Test to students using the
guidelines established pursuant to subsection A of this section or
from nationally accepted fitness testing programs designed for
school-aged children that test cardiovascular fitness, muscular
strength and endurance, flexibility, and body composition.
C. School districts shall utilize student performance results
on the Presidential Fitness Test to:
1. Promote the physical and mental benefits of daily movement,
exercise, and good nutrition;
2. Modify physical activity opportunities offered to students;
and
3. Encourage participation in physical activities available to
students inside and outside the school setting.
ENR. S. B. NO. 1437 Page 2

D. The State Board of Education may promulgate rules to
implement the provisions of this section.
SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
ENR. S. B. NO. 1437 Page 3

